who has to approve

10:06.772 --> 10:08.440
all those hours...
- Yeah.

10:08.599 --> 10:10.350
- And know where it's going...
- Right.

10:10.443 --> 10:12.018
- The best way to explain it
to you on this car

10:12.111 --> 10:13.603
is to show it to you.

10:13.687 --> 10:15.280
These floor pans were gone,

10:15.439 --> 10:17.198
so you can see
that's all been cut out,

10:17.283 --> 10:18.700
and that's gonna be replaced.

10:18.784 --> 10:20.535
But, brother,
it just goes on from there.

10:20.620 --> 10:22.954
I mean, you can see they're
already working on rockers

10:23.039 --> 10:24.697
and stuff here throughout.

10:24.790 --> 10:26.949
I mean, the guys are already
stitching them up,

10:27.034 --> 10:28.376
but, you know,
it's everywhere, man.

10:28.461 --> 10:31.379
I mean,
there is just rust everywhere.

10:31.464 --> 10:34.966
The bottom of this quarter
panel, how wraps underneath,

10:35.051 --> 10:37.719
it's just toast,
I mean, throughout.

10:37.803 --> 10:40.797
And it's literally everywhere.

10:40.881 --> 10:42.882
- It's just amazing when you
blast these things,

10:42.966 --> 10:45.310
the stuff you find--
I mean, wow.

10:45.469 --> 10:47.062
- Oh, yeah.

10:47.221 --> 10:49.064
It is amazing, 'cause,
you know, when the car came in,

10:49.223 --> 10:50.640
it looked like a solid.

10:50.724 --> 10:52.067
I mean, it looked like
an entire car.

10:52.151 --> 10:53.726
- Yeah.
- But, you know, it's like

10:53.819 --> 10:55.895
you said, man, you start
blasting them down...

10:55.979 --> 10:57.146
- Mm-hmm.

10:57.239 --> 10:58.981
- They reveal
what they're hiding, man.

10:59.075 --> 11:00.566
- Yeah.
- And this one is hiding

11:00.651 --> 11:02.577
a whole lot of rust.

11:02.662 --> 11:04.329
